{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is cross-module handoff: three collectors -> aggregation layer -> summary input payload. A unit test of one function can miss dropped/overwritten fields during wiring. Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified because behavior text only requires verifying assembled content, not real network/OS/subprocess behavior; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because correctness does not depend on model output, only on input composition before generation.","test_description":"Run collectors as wired modules with deterministic fakes for each source client, execute data-collection + assembly path, and assert the payload handed to summary generation contains all three source sections with correct mapping.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is error propagation across modules (source adapter failure -> report builder fallback note -> pipeline continues). Unit is too low because fallback can fail at module boundaries. Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified because unavailability can be reproduced by in-process client failure stubs; no real network/OS primitive is required by behavior text. Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because this is fallback orchestration, not model judgment quality.","test_description":"Wire the report pipeline with one source client stubbed to raise an unavailable error and the other two returning data; assert run completes, output includes `data unavailable` only for the failed section, and process does not abort.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior directly evaluates summary content quality/faithfulness, which depends on real model decisions (possible run-to-run variation). Deterministic stubs would mask misrepresentation/hallucination failures. Rejected higher level: Workflow is disqualified because behavior covers one generation step’s output quality, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Feed representative structured inputs with known key values to the real summary-generation model, run repeated trials, and score whether produced narrative preserves required facts/figures within acceptance thresholds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real failure boundary includes external delivery infrastructure (email transport/inbox) and end-to-end process behavior. In-process fakes can hide auth, transport, MIME, and delivery routing failures. Rejected higher levels: Agentic is disqualified by behavior text focus on delivery to inbox, not summary-quality correctness; Workflow is disqualified because no multi-agentic decision chain is being validated.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled report script end-to-end against real reachable service endpoints (or production-like test instances) and a real test mailbox, then assert message arrives in configured recipient inbox with expected report artifact.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.83,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core risk is state handoff across runs: delivery failure -> local persistence -> next run reload/retry. This can be caught by wiring modules with failing then recovering mail client and real local test filesystem. Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified because behavior does not require real network outage semantics; unreachable service can be represented by client errors while still validating persistence/retry logic. Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because correctness is retry/persistence orchestration, not model output decisions.","test_description":"Run pipeline twice in test harness: first run with mail client returning unreachable error, assert report is written to fallback file; second run with mail client healthy, assert persisted report is retried and sent, and retry state is cleared.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.19,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
